title.rendered: Rajasthan vs Punjab, Indian T20 League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Rajasthan: Yashasvi Jaiswal, Jos Buttler*, Sanju Samson (c & wk), Devdutt Padikkal, Riyan Parag, Shimron Hetmyer*, Ravichandran Ashwin, Jason Holder*, Trent Boult*, Yuzvendra Chahal, KM Asif

Punjab: Shikhar Dhawan (c), Prabhsimran Singh, Bhanuka Rajapaksa*, Jitesh Sharma (wk), Sikandar Raza*, Sam Curran*, Shahrukh Khan, Nathan Ellis/Kagiso Rabada*, Harpreet Brar, Rahul Chahar, Arshdeep Singh

Pitch Report

Venue: Barsapara Cricket Stadium, Guwahati

(Based on the last three competitive T20s)

1st innings average score: 202

2nd innings average score: 161

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 100%

Batting 2nd: —

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Yuzvendra Chahal is the best strike bowler in the spin department in the league. He has the best strike rate (16.9) – even better than Rashid Khan – by a spinner who has taken over 100 wickets in the league.

Such has been Jos Buttler’s consistency in 2023 that he made it to the Best11 in 12 of 15 competitive T20s, scoring 556 runs at 40 and grabbing nine catches.

Devdutt Padikkal averages 27 at the venue, also generating bonus points for 15 boundaries in four games.

Sanju Samson’s remarkable performances against Punjab time and again have been keeping fantasy players happy: 658 runs at 41 including five thirties, two fifties, and a hundred.

Shikhar Dhawan’s strike rate may not impress the T20 fanatics, but an average of 35 after 207 games in the league is encouraging enough for fantasy players.

Sikandar Raza’s all-round skills – especially his off-spin – will play a key role on this wicket. The fact that there are three southpaws in Rajasthan’s batting unit further strengthens his case.

Jitesh Sharma’s numbers in the league are quite commendable. Despite going at a strike rate of 166, his 255 runs have come at an average of 28.

Three bowlers in the bowling category made it to the Best11 in four of the last five games: Trent Boult, Arshdeep Singh, and Rahul Chahar. 

To further spice it up, Arshdeep has taken 12 wickets in only five games against Rajasthan. Meanwhile, Boult has taken an average of 18 wickets per season in the last three years.

In the last three games at the venue, spinners accounted for 67% of the wickets.
